      "message": "This is not needed since we have a constructor function (New) that can do initialization. sync.Once is useful if we allow cache :\u003d Cache{} (which we shouldn\u0027t, since we have New).\n\nIf you prefer to keep sync.Once, then remove New(). Having two ways to construct object is frustrating for the users (how do they know which one to use?)",
